You could save the page, paste the following into a file and run &quot;perl file savedpage.html > fixedpage.html&quot; and open that instead.<p>I&#x27;m sure a Javascript programmer would come up with some better solution instead?...<p><pre><code>  local $/;
  $_= <>;
  s/<(.*?)>/$id++; $t{$id}=$1; &quot;<$id>&quot;/sge;
  s/([.?!][^\w].*?)([a-zA-Z])/$1.uc($2)/sge;
  s/<(.*?)>/&quot;<$t{$1}>&quot;/sge;
  s/(<[pP]\b[^>]*>\s*)([a-z])/$1.uc($2)/sge;
  print;
</code></pre>
Edit: changed \. to [.?!] in line 4.
